Durban - Police have confirmed that the mother of the baby who was found abandoned at Engen garage at uShaka, Point was arrested on Thursday afternoon. KZN police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said the 21 year old was arrested in the Point area and is due to appear in the Durban Magistrate's Court on Monday. Gwala said the two week old baby was immediately taken to a nearby hospital for medical attention. She said the infant remained in a place of safety. The woman faces charges of child abandonment. Sentencing is imminent for a Verulam mother who pleaded guilty to dumping her newborn in a garbage bag on the side of the road even though she knew the newborn was alive. The woman was convicted of attempted murder. In a separate incident a Newlands East mother who threw her baby into a stormwater drain earlier this year is also facing trial. She is out on bail. POST